      <div id="item-3-2">
        <h5>Rivalary</h5>
        <p>
The rivalry among Istanbul's Beşiktaş JK, Fenerbahçe SK, and Galatasaray SK is storied, but the Galatasaray-Fenerbahçe derby stands out as one of football's most intense clashes worldwide. Leading up to these matches, tensions escalate dramatically, fueled by media hype and the fervor of passionate fans. The outcomes of these derbies hold significant weight, often dictating the fate of coaches who either earn adoration or face dismissal based on their results.
<br><br>
Graeme Souness became an immortal figure for Galatasaray supporters following a defining moment. After securing a cup victory against Fenerbahçe, Souness symbolically planted Galatasaray's yellow-red flag right in the heart of Fenerbahçe's stadium. This bold act earned him the moniker "Ulubatli Souness," drawing parallels to "Ulubatli Hasan," a soldier under Sultan Mehmed II, who planted the Ottoman Empire's flag in Constantinople, affirming the city's conquest. Souness's daring gesture solidified his legacy among the devoted followers of Galatasaray, immortalizing him in their folklore.</p>
      </div>
